## Bug Confirmed: Style Bug in Virtual Scroll Page

The comparison is stark:
- **Data Sources**: Dropdown has proper white background, border, and visual container styling
- **Virtual Scroll**: Dropdown has a **transparent background** (no background-color CSS applied to the `ng-dropdown-panel`)

The items are visible because the page itself has a white background, but the dropdown panel itself is transparent/unstyled. If the page had a colored background, the dropdown items would appear to float over the background color with no containment.

